ğŸ” Introduction to Data Migration
âœ… What is data migration, and why is it important?
Data migration is the process of transferring data from one system (e.g., SQL databases like MySQL or PostgreSQL) to another system (e.g., NoSQL databases like MongoDB).
It is important because:
Systems evolve and scale
Companies adopt new technologies
Performance and flexibility requirements change
Legacy systems need modernization

âœ… Key differences between SQL and NoSQL

| SQL (Relational)   | NoSQL (Non-Relational)           |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------- |
| Fixed schema       | Flexible / dynamic schema        |
| Tables & rows      | Documents, key-value, graphs     |
| Strong consistency | Often eventual consistency       |
| Joins supported    | No joins (usually embedded data) |
| Vertical scaling   | Horizontal scaling               |

ğŸ›  Overview of DLoader
âœ… What is DLoader?
DLoader is a data migration tool that helps move data from SQL databases to NoSQL databases (like MongoDB).
It extracts data from relational tables, transforms it into NoSQL-friendly formats (like JSON documents), and loads it into the target NoSQL database.
âœ… Main features of DLoader
Data extraction from SQL databases
Data transformation (schema mapping, denormalization)
Batch loading into NoSQL databases
Error handling and logging
Support for large datasets
Configurable migration rules

ğŸ”„ Migration Process Using DLoader
âœ… Steps to migrate data using DLoader
Analyze the SQL schema (tables, relationships, keys)
Design the NoSQL schema (collections, embedded documents)
Configure DLoader (DB credentials, mappings)
Extract data from SQL database
Transform data to NoSQL format (JSON documents)
Load data into NoSQL database
Validate data accuracy
Test performance and fix issues

âœ… Common challenges & solutions
| Challenge        | Solution                      |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Schema mismatch  | Redesign data model for NoSQL |
| Data duplication | Normalize vs embed carefully  |
| Large datasets   | Migrate in batches            |
| Downtime         | Use incremental migration     |
| Data loss        | Validation & backups          |

ğŸ”„ Data Transformation
âœ… How DLoader handles data transformation
DLoader:
Converts rows into JSON documents
Maps relational tables to NoSQL collections
Handles foreign keys by embedding or referencing
Allows custom transformation rules

âœ… Example of transformation
**SQL (Relational):
Users(id, name)
Orders(id, user_id, total)

**NoSQL (MongoDB):
{
  "_id": 1,
  "name": "Alice",
  "orders": [
    { "id": 101, "total": 250 },
    { "id": 102, "total": 100 }
  ]
}

