ğŸŒ Case Studies & Real-World Examples
âœ… Real-world examples
E-commerce platforms moving from MySQL to MongoDB for scalability
Social media apps migrating to NoSQL for flexible user content
IoT platforms moving to NoSQL for handling massive event streams

âœ… Lessons learned
Redesign data model before migration
Test migration on a small dataset first
Monitor performance
Ensure rollback plans
Data validation is critical

ğŸ§¾ Conclusion
âœ… Advantages of migrating SQL â†’ NoSQL
Better scalability
Flexible schema
Faster writes
Better handling of unstructured data

âŒ Disadvantages
Complex migration process
No joins
Possible data duplication
Requires schema redesign
Learning curve

âœ… When to use DLoader
You should use DLoader when:
Migrating large SQL datasets
Moving to MongoDB or other NoSQL databases
You need automated transformation
You want to reduce manual migration errors
You are modernizing legacy systems

